## Self-Review Phase (REQUIRED)

**Purpose:** Quality gate before completion. Automated checks (debug statements, commit format, placeholder data, orphaned files) run at `orch complete` time — focus on judgment-based checks here.

**Perform these checks before marking complete:**

### Original Symptom Validation (For Bug Fixes)
- [ ] Re-ran the EXACT command/scenario from original issue (same flags, same mode)
- [ ] Documented actual result (not an estimate) via `bd comment`
- [ ] If testing different mode/flag than original, explicitly justified why

**⚠️ Scope Redefinition Warning:** Agents can claim "fix complete" by testing a different scenario. The fix is only verified when the original failing scenario passes.

### Anti-Pattern Detection
- [ ] No god objects (files >300 lines or multiple concerns)
- [ ] No tight coupling, magic values, deep nesting (>3 levels), incomplete work

### Security Review
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, no injection vulnerabilities (SQL, XSS, command, path traversal)

### Test Coverage
- [ ] Happy path, edge cases, and error paths tested

### Deliverables
- [ ] All required deliverables exist, complete, and reported via `bd comment`

### Integration Wiring (CRITICAL)
- [ ] New modules imported, functions called, routes registered, components rendered
- [ ] No orphaned code (new file with 0 imports = red flag)

### Accessibility (if UI changed)
- [ ] Semantic HTML, keyboard-accessible, form labels, alt text, color contrast

### Performance / Error Resilience (if applicable)
- [ ] No N+1 queries, lazy loading where appropriate
- [ ] API failures show helpful error states, components handle null data

### Scope Verification (For refactoring/migration)
- [ ] `rg "old_pattern"` returns 0; `rg "new_pattern"` matches expected count

### Discovered Work
- [ ] Reviewed for discoveries, created beads issues with `triage:review` (or `triage:ready`)
- [ ] Or noted "No discovered work" in completion comment

**When passed:** `bd comments add <beads-id> "Self-review passed - ready for completion"`

